snippet.textDisplay: First off, Cody‘s initial short promo was great. He made clear, why wins and losses matter. Not on a personal note, because over the last couple of shows, we saw how important the match with MJF personally was to Cody. But on a professional note. As a Pro Wrestler every win secures livelyhood and well-being for the wrestler as well as his family. Something that no one in WWE seems to care about. On a second note: Jake the Snake was and still is my favourite wrestler. The most charismatic man in the history of the business. And damn, he can still cut a promo. Thanks for bringing him in, AEW and thank you for an A-Class product from start to finish!!!
